What's the meaning of Se'i?

Se'i is a thinly sliced smoked meat utilizing a mixture of salt and spices which gives a unique taste unlike any bacon. This smoked meat is thicker than common bacon. Se'i usually made from pork or beef. In Kupang, people served se'i with sambal lu'at and jagung bose.

Our Se'i and Sambal Lu'at is originally from Kupang.
